### La muerte de la "Agencia de Estrategia" y el enfoque modular
* **Señal Técnica:** Crítica estructural al modelo tradicional de agencias B2B; transición hacia la creación de activos modulares que se ejecutan directamente.
* **Contenido Crudo:**
> Strategy-only agencies have an 85%+ failure rate. I've seen it over and over again. Agency delivers a gorgeous strategy deck. Then... nothing happens, because: The company gets funding/loses funding, a new product feature launches, or the team just doesn't have the bandwidth to turn 47 slides into actual work.
> 
> In 2026, we'll see the end of discovery phases that eat half the retainer before any work ships. If I'm helping a company with bottom-of-funnel SEO or AEO visibility, we're building the pages together. Modular content that actually ships. Real assets, not just slides. Strategy still matters - but it happens while we're doing the work, not instead of it.

